{"length":345,"page":4,"chunk":24,"chroma:document":". However, if, for example, a team is bowled out after 40 overs in a 50-over match, the other team still has the full 50 overs in which to beat their score. Play in Test matches is usually split into three two-hour sessions, although a minimum number of overs to be bowled in a day is also usually agreed between the sides before a series begins"}